         <div type="translation">
            <p>A. [ - - ]Andreas, son of Androneikianos, who won the boys' running-race in the contest celebrated for the third four-year occurrence of the Aphrodeisiea Philemoniea.</p>
            <p>B. Only the name Philippos can be made out; it seems likely that l.6 includes a reference to the name Molossos, or a derivative.</p>
